body:
Hi all!

I got an error while working with `nuxt.js`, `ais-sort-by`, `ais-instant-search-ssr` and url routing. When page is loaded, I get items in `ais-hits` but afterwards (with some delay) I get errors which are related to addWidget and SortBy. I was looking into code and found out that this functionality can be buggy because this feature is experimental as mentioned in InstantSearch.js file. 

On frontend I get this error: [url](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1x7MaX9T-ZRfhcwaWr3sZ0ezrtXw1XgR-/view?usp=sharing)

I inspected by adding console.log(this.searchParameters) inside `addWidgets` (function of instantSearch lib) and found out that index is `undefined`. [url](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1LWmV1HRrZ3lv5KtfD1MOeIUWkN_WNkEA/view?usp=sharing)

Here I'm getting error: [url](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NszlT9g3_T4XVq95uyFhnFcBk6Ita3iA/view?usp=sharing)

I've done configs and defined index at almost all possible places. In 2nd shared image, you can see that facets (also set by me) are present but index became undefined. I don't know why this is happening.

Index was present previously but it becomes undefined afterwards. **_Btw if I just comment out ais-sort-by then error do not occurs._**

Here is my code for ais-sort-by:

`<ais-sort-by :items=indexConfig />`

```
indexConfig() 
{
return [{ value: process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName, label: this.$t('product_search_list.Relevance')},

{ value: `${process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName}_preis_asc`, label: this.$t('product_search_list.PriceAsc') },

 { value: `${process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName}_preis_desc`, label: this.$t('product_search_list.PriceDesc') },
]
},
```
These are my configs for instant search:

```
import algoliasearch from "algoliasearch/lite";
import { createInstantSearch } from "vue-instantsearch";
import { history as historyRouter } from 'instantsearch.js/es/lib/routers';
import { simple as simpleStateMapping } from 'instantsearch.js/es/lib/stateMappings';

import algolia from '~/services/algoliaClient';

export default function VueInstantSearchPlugin(_, inject) {

  const { instantsearch } = createInstantSearch({
    indexName: process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName,
    searchClient: algolia.algoliaClient,
    routing: {
      router: historyRouter(),
      stateMapping: simpleStateMapping(),
    },
    async searchFunction(helper) {
      // I even tried to set index using helper here but it didn't worked
      await helper.setIndex(process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName);
      helper.state.index;
      helper.search();
    },
    searchParameters: {
      query: _.app.router.query,
      index: process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName,
      disjunctiveFacets: [
        'preis',
        'companyName',
        'productCondition_de',
        'serviceType_de',
        'kategorie',
        'baujahr',
        'priceNumber'
      ],
    },
  });

  inject("instantsearch", instantsearch);
}
```

In nuxt.js we have layouts/default.vue file. In that file I've hydrated instant search inside beforeMount().
Here is the code for it:

```
async beforeMount() {
    const uiState = this.$route.query || {};
    const query = uiState.query || '';
    const page = uiState.page - 1 || 0;
    const $instantsearch = this.$instantsearch;
    let searchState = await this.$instantsearch.findResultsState({
      query,
      page,
      index: process.env.vueAppAlgoliaIndexName,
      facets: [
        'preis',
        'companyName',
        'productCondition_de',
        'serviceType_de',
        'kategorie',
        'baujahr',
        'priceNumber'
      ],
      disjunctiveFacets: [
        'preis',
        'companyName',
        'productCondition_de',
        'serviceType_de',
        'kategorie',
        'baujahr',
        'priceNumber'
      ]
    });
    let algoliaState =  await this.$instantsearch.getState();
    this.$instantsearch.hydrate(algoliaState);
    this.setLoading(false);
```
